entries.meaning: An early station wagon or estate car whose rear bodywork is made of wood, often associated with Southern California surfing culture.
examples: Well, for one thing a Woodie is the last remnant of the true coach-builders' art, dating from a time when wood  […] . But a Woodie is also an icon, emblematic of beaches and surfing and Pacific Coast Highway  […]

entries.meaning: A wooden rollercoaster; an amusement ride whose rails are overlaid upon a wooden track.

examples: She raised her brows. “You got a woodie; I got a wettie. Doesn't mean mine was for yours.”
